The '''Rofeh Cholim Cancer Society (RCCS)''' is an American-based [[organization]] funding [[insurance policy|insurance policies]] for [[cancer patient]]s. It was founded in [[Brooklyn, New York]] in 1997 by [[businessman]] [[Rabbi]] Hershel Koh.<ref>http://www.jewswire.com/.../Rofeh_Cholim_Auction_to_Benefit_Cancer_Patients_Cu..._162.html</ref>

The Society exists through a network of [[fund-raising]] activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/article.php?p=37560|title=$1,805,494.02 Recovered for RCCS Cancer Patients! - Yeshiva World News|date=28 July 2009|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/article.php?p=21858|title=RCCS Wins Half-Million Dollar Insurance Battle - Yeshiva World News|date=4 August 2008|publisher=}}</ref> It also organizes assemblies where [[orthodox Jews]] gather to [[prayer|pray]] on behalf of the sick.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/article.php?p=33630|title=PHOTOS: 3,000 Jam RCCS Dinner to be Mispallel for Cancer Patients - Yeshiva World News|date=29 April 2009|publisher=}}</ref>

